## Introduction

This is the development documentation of the phaseshifts package
and contains Fortran source code used in the EEAS phase shift calculations.
There are call graphs to assist with debugging as well as highlighted source code to follow.

## Compiling

The easiest way to compile the source code is to use the `phaseshifts` python package.

```bash
pip install phaseshifts  # compiles native code with cmake via PEP-517 (or setup.py)
```
